How long have you lived there?

24
00:02:36,170 --> 00:02:44,149
Add these ideas to your answer to make it
longer and more detailed. For example:

25
00:02:44,150 --> 00:02:55,120
"I live in Paris, the capital city. It’s
famous for its landmarks such as the Eiffel

26
00:02:55,120 --> 00:03:04,499
Tower, Notre Dame Cathedral or the Louvre.
It’s also well-known for its food, of course!"

27
00:03:04,499 --> 00:03:14,709
"I live in Shanghai. It’s a huge, bustling,
international city. People from all over the

28
00:03:14,709 --> 00:03:17,810
world live and work there."

29
00:03:17,810 --> 00:03:28,150
"I live in a small town called Banbury. I’ve
been living there for about five years, since

30
00:03:28,150 --> 00:03:33,749
I finished university. It’s a pretty sleepy
place, to be honest."

31
00:03:33,749 --> 00:03:42,099
Let’s look at some useful vocabulary from
these examples which you can use when you

32
00:03:42,099 --> 00:03:43,099
speak.

33
00:03:43,099 --> 00:03:44,220
We said:

34
00:03:44,220 --> 00:03:51,500
"Paris is famous for its landmarks such as
the Eiffel Tower."

35
00:03:51,500 --> 00:03:59,840
Landmarks are famous places or buildings,
like the Eiffel Tower in Paris, the Sydney

36
00:03:59,840 --> 00:04:05,980
Opera House or Christ the Redeemer in Rio.

37
00:04:05,980 --> 00:04:13,608
Does your hometown have any famous landmarks?
What are they called in English?

38
00:04:13,609 --> 00:04:15,540
Next, we said:

39
00:04:15,540 --> 00:04:16,932
"Shanghai is a bustling city."

40
00:04:16,932 --> 00:04:17,932
Do you know what this means?

41
00:04:17,932 --> 00:04:28,340
It means there’s a lot of activity. There
are lots of people, lots of traffic, lots

42
00:04:28,340 --> 00:04:32,140
