50
00:05:21,190 --> 00:05:29,270
Part three: saying what you like about your
hometown.

51
00:05:29,270 --> 00:05:39,890
What’s good about your hometown? What do
you like most about it?

52
00:05:39,890 --> 00:05:46,780
Different people like different things in
a city or town. Let’s look at some example

53
00:05:46,780 --> 00:05:53,109
sentences which express positive feelings:

54
00:05:53,110 --> 00:06:37,840
"I love living in Paris. It’s got such a
rich culture 

55
00:06:37,840 --> 00:06:51,619
and there’s always something interesting
going on."

56
00:06:51,620 --> 00:07:54,540
"Shanghai’s a great place to live. It’s
a real 24-hour city and you can meet people

57
00:07:54,540 --> 00:07:57,110
from all over the world."

58
00:07:57,110 --> 00:08:13,320
"Living in Banbury suits me. It’s a quiet
place and it’s small enough that you can

59
00:08:13,320 --> 00:08:28,960
get to know your neighbours and have a sense
of community."

60
00:08:28,960 --> 00:08:33,309
What’s important for you? Do you want to
live somewhere with a rich culture and a sense

61
00:08:33,309 --> 00:08:34,309
of history, or do you prefer more modern,
international cities? Would you rather live

62
00:08:34,309 --> 00:08:35,309
somewhere larger and more energetic, or somewhere
smaller and more peaceful?

63
00:08:35,309 --> 00:08:36,309
Think about these ideas. You’ll need them
in a minute!

64
00:08:36,309 --> 00:08:37,309
Let’s look at some useful language from
our examples:

65
00:08:37,309 --> 00:08:38,309
"I love living in _______"; "_______’s a
great place to live"; "Living in _______ suits

66
00:08:38,309 --> 00:08:39,309
me."

67
00:08:39,309 --> 00:08:40,309
Of course, you can change these to say what
you want to:

68
00:08:40,309 --> 00:08:41,309
"I quite like living in _______"; "I really
like living in ________";

69
00:08:41,309 --> 00:08:42,309
"I suppose I don’t mind living in ________."

70
00:08:42,309 --> 00:08:43,309
We also saw some useful phrases in our examples:

71
00:08:43,309 --> 00:08:44,310
"It’s got such a rich culture"; "There’s
always something interesting going on"; "It’s

72
00:08:44,310 --> 00:08:45,310
