from all over the world"; "It’s small enough

73
00:08:45,310 --> 00:08:46,310
that you can get to know your neighbours";
"You have a sense of community."

74
00:08:46,310 --> 00:08:47,310
What does that last phrase mean?

75
00:08:47,310 --> 00:08:48,310
If you have a sense of community, it means
people know their neighbours and feel like

76
00:08:48,310 --> 00:08:49,310
they belong to a wider community. Smaller
towns and villages often have a better sense

77
00:08:49,310 --> 00:08:50,310
of community, perhaps because people have
more time to talk to each other and do things

78
00:08:50,310 --> 00:08:51,310
together.

79
00:08:51,310 --> 00:08:52,310
